messages.msgSnippet: In a message dated 5/6/03 9:46:26 AM, nellebelle@charter.net writes:
messages.messageBody:
In a message dated 5/6/03 9:46:26 AM, nellebelle@... writes:

<< Who finally watched Little Shop of Horrors, with Rick & Steve. Reminded
me of the dentists I went to when I was a kid. Seemed they absolutely jammed
that Novocain needle in! >>

That is SUCH a fun movie.

"Suddenly Seymor is SO beautiful and so beautifully done.

Frank Oz is a hell of a director.

That whole set was built, none of it was done outside anywhere.

In "Downtown," watch when he goes up the alley toward the bums climing on the
gate. He timed the steps and the distance to match the music perfectly.
And the rhymes (changing the subject at least as to who I'm praising) in that
song are really intricate and Holly noticed it and told ME about it.

Anyway, it's fun.

Sandra
